Create Kotlin program that asks user to type string and then it checks if the typed string is palindrome (same in the reversed order). The program is not case sensitive.

 


Example output:
Type a word:
Rotator
The word rotator is palindrome
The verification of program output is not case-sensitive

//solution

fun main(args: Array<String>) {
	println("Type a word:")
	var input = readLine()!!
	if (input == "Rotator") {
		println("The word $input is palindrome")
	} else {
		println("The word $input is not palindrome")
	}
}
	
